                    <chapters>
                        <chapter>
                            <title>Ch1: basics</title>
                            <summary>An overview of fundamental programming concepts, including variables, data types, and control structures.</summary>
                            
                            <sections>
                                <section>
                                    <title>Sec 1.1: variables and datatypes<title>
                                    <contents>
                                        <content>Variables are used to store data in programming.</content>
                                        <content>Different data types include integers, strings, and booleans.</content>
                                    </contents>
                                </section>

                                <section>
                                    <title>Sec 1.2: control statements<title>
                                    <contents>
                                        <content>Control structures include loops and conditional statements.</content>
                                        <content>They help in decision-making and repeating tasks efficiently.</content>
                                    <contents>
                                </section>
                            </sections>
                        </chapter>

                        <chapter>
                            <title>Ch2: OOP</title>
                            <summary>A detailed explanation of OOP principles such as encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism.</summary>
                            
                            <sections>
                                <section>
                                    <title>Sec 2.1: Encapsulation</title>
                                    <contents>
                                        <content>Encapsulation is the bundling of data and methods that operate on that data.</content>
                                        <content>It helps in protecting the internal state of an object.</content>
                                    </contents>
                                </section>

                                <section>
                                    <title>Sec 2.2: Inheritance</title>
                                    <contents>
                                        <content>Inheritance is a relation ship.</content>
                                        <content>Help us not repeat the data and take the attributes form parent.</content>
                                    </contents>
                                </section>
                            </sections>
                        </chapter>
                    </chapters>
