                <part>
                    <title>advanced topics</title>
                    <chapters>
                        <chapter>
                            <title>Ch3: Design Patterns</title>
                            <summary>Explores common design patterns used in software development.</summary>
                            
                            <sections>
                                <section>
                                    <title>Sec 3.1: Singleton</title>
                                    <contents>
                                        <content>The Singleton pattern ensures that a class has only one instance.</content>
                                        <content>It is useful for managing shared resources like database connections.</content>
                                    </contents>
                                </section>
                            </sections>
                        </chapter>
                    </chapters>
